Observers:
* A Membership Observer has been added. This observer will check if you or someone in your instance is a member.
* If someone is found to have a membership, Premuim Songs will unlock for current & future players, assuming that the Member is still in the instance when the future players join.
* While I cannot reveal the process of how I'm doing this because Security through Obscurity, all you need to know is that Encrypted Data is loaded in from a remote server & then processed on your device.
* If the observer sees the following, it will not load the Premium songs as a defence mechanism:
* Cannot verify the encrypted data
* Cannot download the encrypted data
* Does not find an active membership on the Current Player or Other Players in your instance
* You can still enter the code & get access to Premuim Songs.

If you try to mess with the data, from the bottom of my mexican sausage, fuck you. Again $2 isn't much!

