NEW CONTROLS!
* Holding the Left Trigger for 1 second will toggle the Screen Overlay
* Holding the Right Trigger for 4 seconds will STOP any current motion. PLEASE BE CAREFUL WHEN HOLDING THE RIGHT TRIGGER.

Tutorial:
* A tutorial section has been added for those that have not played an MMD Map, or want answers to some frequently asked questions

* The tutorial covers of the basics of MMD & VRChat in addition to some *very* importiant things you need to know when playing on my MMD maps.

* The Video Player was written by aparche, the same creator who wrote the MMD Controller. So much better than ProTV!

* The tutorial will send you to the old spawn area if you have completed the tutorial / tell it you have played an MMD map before

QoL:
* Dance Pads between Quest & PC are now in the same location, in reference to the world. This means that when you stand on a dancepad, the MMD Controller won't think you're stepping on 2 dance pads.
* Replaced FullScreenShader (FSS) with FullScreenCanvas (FSC), this allows the player mesh to no longer intersect with the player camera & ruin your photo/video shots.
    * FSC is only available on Desktop Mode / Android Mode. VR is NOT SUPPORTED. VR Users can use the Screen Overlay!
* Added a toggle to disable FSC on Android (idk why the overlay overrides the vrc controls)
    * Just tap the screen to disable the FSC. Toggles to enable FSC are on the MMD Screens
* Added an MMD Mirror to replace the MMD Screen.
    * The Mirror is set to max quality. 1024x resolution & 4x AA. If it still looks bad, I don't know what to tell you.
* Screen Overlay Toggles are now synced with each other & play sounds when toggled.
* Spectator Theatre Screen has new controls & buttons.
* Song Selection Teleport has been added to the Portable Panel
* Modified some quads to better emphasize important texts blocks, such as the Color Codes & Motion Credits
* Updated F.A.Q & Bug text blocks

Observers:
* Several map functions are now being replaced with Observers. Observers "observe" the map for key events & execute special functions. No, this does not mean they spy on you. There's no way to upload data to the internet via Udon.

The following are currently present:
    * Tutorial - Handles functions related to the Tutorial Area, such as remembering if you finished the tutorial.
    * Player Count Observer - Monitors player count & warns current players & future players of that instance that sync issues will occur due to multiple players!
    * Camera Observer - Monitors MMD Playback & forces the MMD Camera to turn on when a motion is playing. This will *hopefully* fix the black screen issue when playing with multiple people.
    * Controller Observer - Monitors controller inputs. The current inputs are the Left & Right trigger, which toggle STOP MMD & Screen Overlay respectively after 4 seconds / 1 second of holding the triggers.
    * Track Progress Observer - Updates the Track Position placed on the MMD Screens & Portable Panel
    * Mirror Observer - Toggles between the MMD Screen & MMD Mirror

NPCs:
* The PC SoapDragons have had various shader options disabled to improve performance
* I want to replace Quest NPCs with those that aren't visually broken. If you know someone that would be okay with having their NPCs on my map, feel free to send them my way!

Song Preview:
* Song Preview now respects the current volume as the maximum volume. Ex: If you set the volume to 10%, the maximum volume during previews will be 10%.
* Fixed Song Preview for audio tracks less than 37 seconds.
* Preview time increased to 12 seconds

Not a Bug, but a Feature:
* When the FullScreenCanvas is enabled & you open your Quick Menu, the FullScreenCanvas will be disabled. This is intentional by VRChat, since the Full Screen Canvas can be used by bad actors & cause pain to the user.

